"<h5>The Health Benefits of Walnuts</h5>
<p> Recent studies show that diets high in nuts, particularly walnuts, are strongly associated with substantially decreased cancer, type-2 diabetes and hypertension prevalance, as well as lower body mass indices. According to <a href='http://www.biomedcentral.com/1741-7015/11/164'>BMC Medicine</a>, those who eat a serving of Walnuts at least 3 times were week have a 45% lower risk of premature mortality than the average person.</p>"